This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques such as principal component analysis (PCA) to analyze the structure of word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings for sentiment analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural machine translation (NMT) models, which are a type of artificial intelligence (AI) and therefore could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of word embeddings for image captioning, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses PCA to analyze the structure of word embeddings, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and therefore could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
